<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <%- include("../../parts/head") %>
</head>

<body class="d-flex flex-column min-vh-10--------------0">

    <!-- Navbar -->
    <%- include("../../parts/navbar") %>

        <!-- Content -->
        <div class="container min-vh-100 bg-light shadow-lg border-start border-end border-dark-subtle">
            <div class="container-content">
                <!-- Hero Image -->
                <div class="row mb-3">
                    <div class="col">
                        <h3>The World of Aeld</h3>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="row gap-3">
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <img class="img-fluid h-50 object-fit-cover rounded mb-3" src="/img/aeld.png" />
                        <p class="mt-3">
                            Aeld is an ancient world shaped by the rise and fall of civilizations. Towering mountain
                            ranges divide kingdoms, vast oceans separate distant continents, and untamed wilderness
                            still claims much of the land between. Though monsters, magic, and forgotten ruins exist,
                            they are exceptions rather than the rule. Most people spend their lives farming fertile
                            valleys, working crowded cities, serving noble houses, or traveling the trade roads that
                            connect the world's great powers.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Despite its ancient history, Aeld remains a living world. Kingdoms compete for influence,
                            faiths spread their teachings, merchants cross continents, and explorers push beyond the
                            edges of civilization in search of wealth, knowledge, and glory. Most adventures begin not
                            in a mythical age of heroes, but in a world that feels familiar: one of hardship and
                            opportunity, where extraordinary people leave their mark on an otherwise
                            ordinary world.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="col-md">
                        <h6 class="lora-semibold">The Commonwealth</h6>
                        <p>
                            The Commonwealth encompasses the settled heart of Aeld, where kingdoms, city-states, and
                            free realms stand connected by ancient roads, thriving trade, and centuries of shared
                            history. While every nation governs itself, their borders are bound together by diplomacy,
                            commerce, and necessity. Merchants carry goods across the continent, pilgrims journey
                            between sacred sites, scholars exchange knowledge, and envoys work tirelessly to preserve an
                            often fragile peace.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Bustling cities, fortified castles, quiet villages, prosperous farms, and venerable
                            monasteries dot the landscape, each contributing to a society that has grown steadily atop
                            the foundations of older civilizations. Guilds regulate commerce, noble houses compete for
                            influence, and temples to the Ascendants shape both daily life and affairs of state. Most
                            people will never venture far from these settled lands, finding purpose in honest work,
                            family, and community.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Yet the Commonwealth is far from peaceful. Political rivalries simmer beneath formal
                            alliances, succession disputes threaten entire kingdoms, and ambitious rulers constantly
                            test the limits of old treaties. Criminal syndicates flourish in crowded cities, forgotten
                            cults gather in hidden places, and ancient relics occasionally surface to upset the balance
                            of power. While armies guard the borders, many dangers arise from within.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Beyond the last watchtower and cultivated field lie the Borderlands, where the reach of
                            civilization begins to fade. Here, isolated towns depend upon hunters, wardens, mercenaries,
                            and adventurers to survive. Old roads disappear into forgotten forests, abandoned keeps
                            overlook mountain passes, and the remnants of lost civilizations become increasingly common.
                            Every mile traveled beyond the frontier carries greater risk and greater reward.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            For adventurers, the Commonwealth is more than a backdrop. It is where reputations are
                            earned, allies are found, equipment is purchased, and fortunes are spent. Between
                            expeditions, its cities offer opportunities to train, conduct research, pursue personal
                            ambitions, forge political connections, and prepare for the next journey into the unknown.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>

</body>

</html>